Reasoning: The dominant errors are misclassification and hallucination around what counts as a task, plus weak field-level criteria for task status; schema coverage is missing explicit status boundaries even though status is heavily weighted in evaluation. I chose ADD because no existing rule tells the model how to map transcript evidence to the exact task status enum, and that gap explains repeated mistakes like marking scheduled demos as in_progress and partially working items as not done. I rejected rewording the existing boundary rule because it already addresses extractability broadly, but not the exact status decision needed by the schema.

+ - Set task status from the strongest explicit evidence: use done for completed or working-now statements like finished, completed, working, works, shipped, fixed, or added; use in_progress for active ongoing work like starting, moving on to, or currently working on; use todo for assigned or planned work not yet started and for future scheduled items such as demos or updates; use blocked only when an obstacle is explicitly stated; use paused only when a hold or pause is explicitly stated.
